d_at":"2023-01-17T16:38:14Z","updated_at":"2023-01-17T16:38:14Z","body":"yup, implementing the interface changing what `Levels()` returns does the trick:\r\n\r\n```go\r\npackage main\r\n\r\nimport (\r\n\t\"log/syslog\"\r\n\r\n\tlog \"github.com/sirupsen/logrus\"\r\n\tlogrus_syslog \"github.com/sirupsen/logrus/hooks/syslog\"\r\n)\r\n\r\ntype testHook struct {\r\n\t*logrus_syslog.SyslogHook\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunc (h *testHook) Levels() []log.Level {\r\n\treturn []log.Level{log.WarnLevel}\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunc main() {\r\n\tlog.SetLevel(log.DebugLevel)\r\n\r\n\thook, err := logrus_syslog.NewSyslogHook(\"tcp\", \"localhost:5140\", syslog.LOG_WARNING, \"test\")\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tpanic(err)\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tlog.AddHook(&testHook{hook})\r\n\r\n\t//...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe original behaviour seems very strange to me. You can specify a level but then it is ignored ðŸ¤” \r\nBut at the same time is seems strange nobody noticed this until now... That's why I was thinking I was misusing it","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sirupsen/logrus/issues/comments/1385704708/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"tommyblue","id":122749,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyMjc0OQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/122749?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tommyblue","html_url":"https://github.com/tommyblue","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tommyblue/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tommyblue/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tommyblue/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tommyblue/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tommyblue/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tommyblue/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users